Heat oil in large nonstick skillet on medium heat. Add fish; sprinkle with pepper. Cook 3 min. on each side or until fish is browned on both sides and flakes easily with fork. Remove from skillet; cover to keep warm. Add cooking creme to skillet; cook and stir 2 min. Remove 1/4 cup creme; set aside. Add peas and rice to remaining creme in skillet; cook and stir 3 min. or until heated through. Spoon rice mixture onto platter; top with fish and reserved sauce.